    "title": "Bitcoin 0.15.0.1 can't start from cron without permissions error, copied my blocks folder and chainstate folder",
    "body": "### Describe the issue\r\nBitcoin can't start from cron without permissions error. I've copied my blocks folder and chainstate folder from an older version of bitcoin v0.14.2.0-gfc61c83\r\n\r\n### Can you reliably reproduce the issue?\r\n#### If so, please list the steps to reproduce below:\r\n1. Install Bitcoin Core Daemon version v0.15.0.1 On Ubuntu server 16.04\r\n2. set up cron job under user using crontab -e\r\n@reboot bitcoind -daemon 1> /tmp/bitcoincron.out 2> /tmp/bitcoincron.err\r\n3. run bitcoind -daemon\r\n4. stop bitcoin\r\n5. copy blocks and chainstate folders from older bitcoin install v0.14.2.0-gfc61c83\r\n6. reboot, then cat bitcoincron.err:\r\n```\r\n************************\r\nEXCEPTION: N5boost10filesystem16filesystem_errorE       \r\nboost::filesystem::create_directory: Permission denied: \"/home/user/.bitcoin\"       \r\nbitcoin in AppInit()       \r\n\r\nbitcoind: chainparamsbase.cpp:69: const CBaseChainParams& BaseParams(): Assertion `globalChainBaseParams' failed.\r\nAborted\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What version of bitcoin-core are you using?\r\nBitcoin Core Daemon version bitcoin-0.15.0.1-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar downloaded from the website\r\nand same issue on apt-get install from PPA with version 0.15.0\r\n \r\n### Machine specs:\r\n- OS: Ubuntu Server 16.04\r\n- CPU: Intel(R) Pentium(R) CPU G3220 @ 3.00GHz\r\n- RAM: 4GB\r\n- Disk size: 512 SSD\r\n\r\n### Any extra information that might be useful in the debugging process.\r\n* As above. nothing in .bitcoin/debug.log\r\n* Running bitcoind and bitcoind -daemon from the command line work fine\r\n* in bitcoin.conf using\r\n** server=1\r\n** txindex=1\r\n",
